  "text": "In short, Flanders possesses a vibrant economy with a relatively low level of unemployment while Wallonia has yet to recover from industrial decline. Scholars who find a positive relationship between unemployment and electoral support for the extreme right [CITATION_1] would thus have trouble explaining the Belgian cases. However, if one posits a negative relationship between these variables [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , the success of the VB and the relative weakness of the FN make more sense.",
